{"id":"astro-ph/0306521","submitter":"Axel Brandenburg","authors":"Axel Brandenburg (Nordita), Petri K\\\"apyl\\\"a (KIS, Oulu), Amjed\n  Mohammed (Oldenburg)","title":"Non-Fickian diffusion and tau approximation from numerical turbulence","comments":"10 pages, 7 figs, Physics of Fluids (final version)","journal-ref":"Phys.Fluids 16:1020-1027,2004","doi":"10.1063/1.1651480","report-no":"NORDITA 2003-34 AP","categories":"astro-ph nlin.CD physics.flu-dyn","license":null,"abstract":"  Evidence for non-Fickian diffusion of a passive scalar is presented using\ndirect simulations of homogeneous isotropic turbulence. The results compare\nfavorably with an explicitly time-dependent closure model based on the tau\napproximation. In the numerical experiments three different cases are\nconsidered: (i) zero mean concentration with finite initial concentration flux,\n(ii) an initial top hat profile for the concentration, and (iii) an imposed\nbackground concentration gradient. All cases agree in the resulting relaxation\ntime in the tau approximation relating the triple correlation to the\nconcentration flux. The first order smoothing approximation is shown to be\ninapplicable.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 25 Jun 2003 18:19:13 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Sat, 31 Jan 2004 20:23:37 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Wed, 10 Mar 2004 03:45:32 GMT"}],"update_date":"2009-11-10"}
